# Go Constants
just like the name constant, it does not change.

### Constant Rules

    Constant names follow the same naming rules as variables
    Constant names are usually written in uppercase letters
    Constants can be declared both inside and outside of a function.

### Constant Types

    Typed constants. the type constant tells if it is an integer or a string .

    
    Untyped constants. This does not tell, it just declare it without specifying if it is an int or not

Constant can be decared multiples times in a code  in a blocked format


